- VSCode Version: 1.2.0
- OS Version: Win 10 Pro Version 1511

Steps to Reproduce:
1.  Write this code:

```
    Observable.of(this.currentTask)
        .filter(_key => _key !== undefined)
        .flatMap(_key => this.taskService.getTask(_key))
        .subscribe(
            task => {
                this.task = task;
                this.loading = false;
            },
            error => console.error(error)
        );
```
1. Press `shift+alt+f` (format code)
2. VSCode will change indentation to:

```
    Observable.of(this.currentTask)
        .filter(_key => _key !== undefined)
        .flatMap(_key => this.taskService.getTask(_key))
        .subscribe(
        task => {
            this.task = task;
            this.loading = false;
        },
        error => console.error(error)
        );
```

- VSCode Version: 0.1.2
- OS Version: Mac OSX El Capitan

Steps to Reproduce:
1.  Paste this into a new file with Sass syntax:

``` scss
@each $color, $hex in $colors {

  .color-#{$color} {
    color: $hex;
  }

  .border-#{$color} {
    border: 1px solid $hex;
    border-radius: 2px;

  }

  @each $side in ('top', 'left', 'right', 'bottom') {
    .border-#{$side}-#{$color} {
      border-#{$side}: 1px solid $hex;
      border-radius: 2px;
    }
  }

  .background-#{$color} {
    background: $hex;
  }
}
```

